                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13986879" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 19:06:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I went and checked if shuffle has the same problem (it should) and it&apos;s broken in a similar way: it never deletes things from the &apos;schedule&apos; even though it moves them.  I do see the system.local table flushing though, so I suspect these are related.  Ring output also doesn&apos;t reflect any changes even though the log indicates all the tokens moved.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13986886" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 1 May 2014 19:14:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;At least if you do writes and then restart, everything still works, like shuffle didn&apos;t actually happen.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988183" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 20:25:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem here stemmed from the comment &quot;no need to persist, token/ip did not change&quot; which is not actually true; only the endpoint is being checked, the token could have changed.  Patch to persist under this condition regardless.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988202" author="tjake" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 20:35:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 if the dtest passes now &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13988221" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 2 May 2014 20:53:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
